# ============================================================================
# STRICT ALLOWLIST .gitignore (deny by default)
# ============================================================================
# Philosophy:
# - Everything is ignored unless explicitly allowed below.
# - Safer for sensitive repos and cleaner than long blocklists.
#
# How to add a new tracked folder:
# 1) Add BOTH lines in the "Allowlisted project content" section:
#      !path/to/folder/
#      !path/to/folder/**
# 2) Immediately add secret/build re-exclusions AFTER the include lines, e.g.:
#      path/to/folder/.env
#      path/to/folder/.env.*
#      path/to/folder/dist/
#      path/to/folder/node_modules/
#
# Rule ordering matters:
# - Later rules win.
# - Re-exclusions for secrets/build outputs MUST come after allowlist rules.
#
# Verification (run before first commit and after edits):
#   git check-ignore -v <path>      # explain why a path is ignored
#   git ls-files --others -i --exclude-standard   # list ignored-but-present files
#   git add -n .                    # dry-run to preview what would be staged
# ============================================================================
#
# Project notes:
#   - TypeScript/Node.js monorepo with three top-level domains:
#       mcp_node/    — 7 SDK client libraries (node-auvik, node-blumira, etc.)
#       mcp_servers/ — 10 MCP server packages (auvik-mcp, cipp-mcp, etc.)
#       plugins/     — 12 domain-cluster Claude plugin definitions (marketplace)
#   - *.mcpb bundle files are NOT tracked — GitHub's 100 MB hard limit blocks pushes
#     once bundled node_modules grow past it. Bundles are published as GitHub Release
#     artifacts; rebuild locally with `npm run pack:mcpb` inside each server dir.
#   - .env files exist in some mcp_servers/* subdirs — ALL are ignored by default
#   - .env.example / .env.template are intentionally tracked as safe templates
#   - .claude/ dirs contain Claude Desktop config that may hold session tokens
# ============================================================================


# ============================================================================
# SECTION 2 — Deny everything (deny by default; all later sections refine this)
# ============================================================================

*
/**
/.*
/.*/
.DS_Store


# ============================================================================
# SECTION 3 — Global sensitive-file protection
# (these patterns are explicit even though * already denies them — belt and
#  suspenders so the intent survives partial edits of this file)
# ============================================================================

# ---- Env files ----
.env
.env.*
!.env.template
!.env.example
!.env.sample

# ---- Keys and certs ----
*.key
*.pem
*.p12
*.pfx
*.crt
*.cer
*.der
*.asc
*.gpg
id_rsa
id_ed25519
id_ecdsa
*_rsa
*_ed25519

# ---- Generic secret markers ----
*.secret
*.secrets
secrets.json
secrets.yaml
secrets.yml
credentials.json
credentials.yaml
credentials.yml
**/secrets/
**/*.secret
**/*.secrets

# ---- Cloud / provider credentials ----
.aws/
.azure/
.gcloud/
gcloud-key.json
service-account*.json
*serviceaccount*.json
firebase-adminsdk*.json

# ---- Tokens, sessions, history that often leak secrets ----
.netrc
.npmrc
.pypirc
.terraformrc
*.tfstate
*.tfstate.*
.terraform/
.bash_history
.zsh_history
.python_history
.node_repl_history

# ---- Common dump / backup leaks ----
*.sql
*.dump
*.bak
*.backup
*.orig

# ---- Downloaded archives that should never be committed ----
*.zip
*.tar.gz
*.tgz
*.tar


# ============================================================================
# SECTION 4 — Allowlisted project content
# (every entry here is intentional; add new tracked paths here, not elsewhere)
# ============================================================================

# ---- Repo / meta ----
!.gitignore
!.gitattributes
!.fallowrc.json
!.env.template
!README.md
!CLAUDE.md
!AGENTS.md
!LICENSE
!CHANGELOG.md
!CONTRIBUTING.md
!SECURITY.md
!CLA.md

# ---- Root scripts ----
!test-mcp-tools.mjs

# ---- CI/CD at repo root (if added in future) ----
!.github/
!.github/**

# ---- mcp_node — TypeScript SDK client libraries ----
# Covers: node-auvik, node-blumira, node-ninjaone, node-paylocity,
#         node-spanning, node-threatlocker, node-vanta
# Section 5 strips dist/, node_modules/, coverage/, .env* from within.
!mcp_node/
!mcp_node/**

# ---- mcp_servers — MCP server packages ----
# Covers: auvik-mcp, blumira-mcp, cipp-mcp, connectwise-manage-mcp,
#         kaseya-spanning-backup-mcp, knowbe4-mcp, ninjaone-mcp,
#         paylocity-mcp, threatlocker-mcp, vanta-mcp, _shared/
# Section 5 strips dist/, node_modules/, .env*, .archive/, *.zip from within.
!mcp_servers/
!mcp_servers/**

# ---- plugins — Claude plugin definitions ----
# 12 domain clusters: atlas, it-operations, security-compliance, microsoft-365,
#   hr-payroll, finance, engineering, design, data, customer-support,
#   product-management, productivity.
# Each plugin contains: .claude-plugin/plugin.json, commands/*.md, skills/*.
# Connector clusters also ship .mcp.json, hooks/, and mcp/<name>.mcpb bundles
# (the .mcpb re-include is in Section 5; loose dist/node_modules stay ignored).
!plugins/
!plugins/**

# ---- skills — canonical skill definitions (SKILL.md, references/, hooks/, scripts/, agents/) ----
!skills/
!skills/**

# ---- .claude-plugin — root marketplace manifest ----
# Note: /.* and /.*/ in SECTION 2 block root-level dotdirs; we must re-allow this one.
!.claude-plugin/
!.claude-plugin/**

# ---- docs — atlas documentation SSOT (CHANGELOG, ROADMAP, plans, specs, evidence,
#      architecture, features, lessons, audits, wiki, reference_files). Atlas builds and
#      maintains these as the project's single source of truth, so they must be tracked.
#      Only the SSOT subtree is allowlisted: large vendored doc-site clones under docs/
#      (cline, aider, vendors, gemini-cli, frameworks, claude-code, ...), each with its own
#      nested .git, stay ignored as local reference material, not project history.
#      Do NOT add a blanket !docs/** — that would try to commit those nested repos.
!docs/
!docs/*.md
!docs/architecture/
!docs/architecture/**
!docs/features/
!docs/features/**
!docs/specs/
!docs/specs/**
!docs/audits/
!docs/audits/**
!docs/lessons/
!docs/lessons/**
!docs/wiki/
!docs/wiki/**
!docs/plans/
!docs/plans/**
!docs/evidence/
!docs/evidence/**
!docs/reference_files/
!docs/reference_files/**
# This repo's existing owned doc dirs (small, no nested repo):
!docs/standards/
!docs/standards/**
!docs/superpowers/
!docs/superpowers/**


# ============================================================================
# SECTION 5 — Re-exclude generated, local, and machine-specific artifacts
# MUST physically appear after all allowlist (!) rules — later rules win.
# ============================================================================

# ---- Node / TypeScript build outputs ----
**/node_modules/
**/node_modules/**
**/node_modules.nosync.noindex/
**/node_modules.nosync.noindex/**
**/node_modules.nosync.noindex

# ---- Atlas ephemeral run state (orchestration scratch; never durable) ----
docs/.run/
docs/.run/**

# ---- Safety: keep any nested git repo / vendored doc-site clone under docs/ out ----
# The docs allowlist above never includes these; this is belt-and-suspenders so a
# future blanket !docs/** can never drag a gigabyte of nested .git repos into history.
docs/**/.git/
docs/**/.git/**

**/dist/
**/dist/**
**/build/
**/build/**
**/.next/
**/.nuxt/
**/.turbo/
**/.vite/
**/.cache/
**/*.tsbuildinfo
**/coverage/
**/coverage/**
**/.eslintcache

# ---- Generated knowledge-graph output (graphify skill) ----
# These cache files embed absolute /Users/<name>/... paths — never commit them.
**/graphify-out/
**/graphify-out/**

# ---- Downloaded / auto-generated archives ----
mcp_servers/*.zip
mcp_servers/**/*.zip

# ---- MCP server archive folder (historical snapshots, not source) ----
mcp_servers/.archive/
mcp_servers/.archive/**

# ---- Per-project env re-exclusions ----
# The broad !mcp_servers/** above would un-ignore .env files; these lines
# re-exclude all .env variants across every subdirectory at any depth.
**/.env
**/.env.*
# Re-preserve safe template / example variants after the broad .env.* sweep:
!**/.env.template
!**/.env.example
!**/.env.sample

# ---- Claude Desktop config (may contain API keys / session tokens) ----
**/.claude/
**/.claude/**

# ---- Log files ----
*.log
**/*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# ---- OS / editor noise ----
**/.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store/**
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
**/.idea/
**/.vscode/
!**/.vscode/settings.json.example
**/*.swp
**/*.swo

# ---- Python baseline (not in active use; kept for hostile-default coverage) ----
**/__pycache__/
**/__pycache__/**
**/*.py[cod]
**/.venv/
**/venv/
**/.pytest_cache/
**/.pytest_cache/**
**/.mypy_cache/
**/.ruff_cache/


# ============================================================================
# Pre-commit verification checklist:
#   1. git status                                 # nothing unexpected staged?
#   2. git check-ignore -v .env                   # confirm secrets are ignored
#   3. git ls-files | grep -E '\.(env|key|pem)$'  # confirm no secrets tracked
#   4. git diff --cached                          # review staged content
# If ANY secret-like file appears in steps 1, 3, or 4 — STOP and investigate.
# ============================================================================

# Built MCPB bundles in mcp_servers/ are NOT tracked (rebuilt locally / shipped via Releases).
*.mcpb
# EXCEPTION: connector bundles shipped INSIDE a plugin are tracked on purpose.
# Each MUST stay small (~3 MB): the slimmed pack excludes the dev toolchain and
# the iCloud node_modules.nosync.noindex twin (see mcp_servers/_shared/pack-mcpb.js).
# A bundle that balloons to tens of MB means the pack regressed - a marketplace
# fetch then stalls, and any single file over GitHub's 100 MB hard limit rejects
# the whole push. Re-pack with the canonical packer before committing; never
# commit a multi-tens-of-MB .mcpb. The plugin extracts each bundle to
# ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA} on first run, which is what makes connectors work after a
# marketplace install. Later rules win, so this re-include must stay after the
# *.mcpb exclusion above.
!plugins/*/mcp/*.mcpb
.orchestrator/
.fallow/
